Content: **Strict Fundraising Rules (it’s the law):**
We can only fundraise on behalf of: Democratic National Committee, Harris Victory Fund or Harris for President directly. 
We can recruit for "non-official events" that are hosted by partner organizations or volunteers in ⁠non-official-events-only. We can recruit into anything that is listed on events.democrats.org or a state democratic party's mobilize.
Rule 3 Note > Relevance: Do not post links to petitions or other calls to action that haven’t been approved by Staff. This forum is not intended for debates. Additionally, do not attempt to raise funds or share fundraising links for any entity besides the Democratic National Committee. Using this server to raise funds for yourself, another candidate, or another organization violates campaign finance law and is strictly prohibited. Anyone who violates the rules is subject to removal or time out.
When in doubt, ask @Community Moderator.

We can only fundraise on behalf of: Democratic National Committee, Harris Victory Fund or Harris for President directly.

Additionally, do not attempt to raise funds or share fundraising links for any entity besides the Democratic National Committee. Using this server to raise funds for yourself, another candidate, or another organization violates campaign finance law and is strictly prohibited. Anyone who violates the rules is subject to removal or time out.

Anyone who violates the rules is subject to removal or time out.

Message ID: 1277100894605017219
Message Type: Default
Reply to: None
Timestamp: 2024-08-25T03:03:00.661+00:00
Author: DanQ, TX (n7hq)
Author Id: 651292239300919296
Avatar URL: assets\0-EB806.png
Content: Ex-Republican here. I’ve been using Politifact for fact-checking and created a simple visual aid based on over 9,000 individual ratings. It’s been super helpful when discussing the importance of integrity in our politics.

- The Republican/Democrat categories include presidential candidates and running mates only (Biden included).
- Both Vance and Walz have limited data (14-Vance, 3-Walz ratings).
- The Media category is heavily skewed by social media, online, and email sources. Three pundits are included: Maddow, Carlson, and Hannity. Adding Rachel Maddow improves the balance in this category.

I’ve got additional graphs and the data available if anyone’s interested. Not sure about the rules for sharing here, so feel free to reach out for more details if you are interested.
--------------------

--- Message ---
Message ID: 1277119920567746571
Message Type: Reply
Reply to: 1277100894605017219
Timestamp: 2024-08-25T04:18:36.804+00:00
Author: Evan B (evo_devo)
Author Id: 109848744362508288
Avatar URL: assets\039a1a53b4ecb5d1413b1170cef883d6-5397F.png
Content: How was each data point collected? Is this a personal persons belief by party or what
--------------------

--- Message ---
Message ID: 1277125555262591080
Message Type: Reply
Reply to: 1277119920567746571
Timestamp: 2024-08-25T04:41:00.22+00:00
Author: DanQ, TX (n7hq)
Author Id: 651292239300919296
Avatar URL: assets\0-EB806.png
Content: Thank you for your question, Evan. The Poynter Institute for Media Studies, established in 1975 in St. Petersburg, Florida, is a non-profit journalism school and research organization. It owns the Tampa Bay Times and operates the International Fact-Checking Network and PolitiFact. Their methodology for fact-checking is detailed here: https://www.politifact.com/article/2018/feb/12/principles-truth-o-meter-politifacts-methodology-i/.

The Institute maintains web pages for political figures and social media outlets, which track PolitiFact fact-checks. These checks typically begin with statements that gain media attention or appear in online postings. I accessed candidate pages (here is Joe's https://www.politifact.com/personalities/joe-biden/) and lists of mainstream social media pages, then recorded the fact-check results in a spreadsheet, then graphed it.

This specific graph exclusively represents data from presidential candidates, including Joe Biden, Kamala Harris, Tim Walz, Donald Trump, and J.D. Vance, so the party affiliations are factual and not based on opinion. The media data is aggregated from various sources with combined fact-check scoring from platforms and figures such as X Posts, Facebook Posts, Instagram, Viral Images, Bloggers, TikTok, Threads, PunditFact, Tucker Carlson, Sean Hannity, and Rachel Maddow. Each source has its respective PolitiFact page, ensuring the scoring is accurate as of last weekend. All this data has been categorized under the umbrella term "Media" and is neither scored as Democrat or Republican.
--------------------

Content: ### Quick Guide: Handling 🧌 Trolls 🧌 on Our Server
If you encounter a troll, spammer, scammer, or any disruptive behavior, please follow these steps to help keep our community safe and welcoming:

**Capture Evidence:**
Take a screenshot of the troll's offending message or action. Make sure to include both the username and any nickname the user might have in the server.
**Block the Troll:**
Protect yourself from further disruption by blocking the troll. This will prevent them from sending you direct messages or reacting to your posts.
**Report the Incident:**
Share the screenshot and details of the incident with a moderator. This helps us take swift action and keep the community secure.

By following these steps, you play an essential role in maintaining a positive environment for everyone. Thank you for your vigilance and support!

--- Message ---
Message ID: 1280889255605829643
Message Type: Reply
Reply to: 1280866618569920575
Timestamp: 2024-09-04T13:56:36.308+00:00
Author: Joey (joeyv120)
Author Id: 693617747606634548
Avatar URL: assets\2440f6e894bf278df9d7f7595ea34582-24E50.png
Content: Yes you can share these. Using the Sharing option directly will link back to the image stored here on Discord, which works, but links can break, and linked images don’t always appear well on some platforms. I instead recommend you Long-Press on the image, select **Save Image**, then share it from the photos library on your device to Twitter or other social media. The Save option is also available with a  Tap on the image and tapping the three dots menu dropdown.
--------------------

We can only fundraise on behalf of: Democratic National Committee, Harris Victory Fund or Harris for President directly.

Anyone who violates the rules is subject to removal or time out.

We can only fundraise on behalf of: Democratic National Committee, Harris Victory Fund or Harris for President directly.

Content: i decided to fact check this myself and those numbers are technically correct based on averages. hate crimes kept going up, then peaked in October 2023, then _plummeted_ by December. even at that peak they weren't pandemic-levels, which were the highest peak in hate crimes in the past 10 years based on data. so, even though they've overall increased, looks like they're still declining, thanks to news reports! so good news is, even though they went up on average, they're starting to decline again.

other than that, it's pretty accurate. almost everything went down. in fact i'd argue some of those went down by _more._

except vehicle thefts. for some reason. those went up 12.6%. [here's the sauce](https://cde.ucr.cjis.gov/LATEST/webapp/#/pages/home)

--- Message ---
Message ID: 1291252772964143115
Message Type: Default
Reply to: None
Timestamp: 2024-10-03T04:17:31.391+00:00
Author: Jen Medeiros [CA] • [Lead Mod] (starkittynmom)
Author Id: 1276944250491113656
Avatar URL: assets\a_2aba4b7f19fcab5fe5391fcdb73d735d-D670A.gif
Content: **Discord Community Norms**
While we come from diverse backgrounds, we are all here united by our shared commitment to electing Vice President Kamala Harris and Democrats up and down the ticket. Radical inclusivity is critical to strengthening this community and our collective effort. Finding common ground with people who differ from us is how we create real, positive change. To that end, we agree to make every effort to the following terms:

Respect: We foster a culture that prioritizes respect, safety, good faith, and thoughtfulness at all times. We will not tolerate harassment of any kind.
Inclusivity: We agree to use language that reflects the values of inclusivity and respect for other members. Never use language that excludes others or negatively reflects on our efforts.
Relevance: Do not post links to petitions or other calls to action that haven’t been approved by Staff. This forum is not intended for debates. Additionally, do not attempt to raise funds or share fundraising links for any entity besides the Democratic National Committee. Using this server to raise funds for yourself, another candidate, or another organization violates campaign finance law and is strictly prohibited.
Teamwork: **Assume best intentions** in our interactions. By collaborating with empathy and a shared focus on our mission, we strengthen our collective efforts.
--------------------

Author: Alex McLand (TX) - MOD (tiredforever)
Author Id: 225877156247502850
Avatar URL: assets\a398fe8179da009dde0ef2cbe8b85b49-F1629.png
Content: yes! memes have a specific layout/phrase/idea with them. for example: this "awkward monkey" meme. the message here is that someone or something (like a conversation) happened that was awkward, maybe even uncomfortable. the monkey is reacting to that 'awkward' thing.

i'll use a line from JD Vance for this: the monkey is everyone's reaction to his statement. here, the "awkward monkey" is relatable. 

memes all have a layout that work something like this: there's a format/idea/phrase they usually use, and that's part of the joke. the second part is being relatable, and the third part is sending the message
--------------------

Content: memes are more about spreading a message, usually with a slogan or theme. they're not usually for information, but to be relatable and generate an emotional response that gets someone to engage with it. 

here's one i made as an example. it's a little in line with 'humor' while also using a template that's recognizable. 

more than anything, the goal is to be simple, catchy, and inspiring.

Content: oh no!! please do not give up. See any breaking news you think would make a fun meme? Make it fresh and about Harris, Walz, endorsements, upcoming appearances, campaign issues, appearances, factual, favorable, and timely. Harris vs.Trump policy comparisons are OK, but all of the tiring  Trump sucks, negative rants, Part 2 billion we want to avoid. No polls, either. Think positive and uplifting. Avoid fear-based opposition stuff.

While we welcome a wide variety of humor, we do want to keep memes respectful of all people and groups, especially marginalized and oppressed groups. Also in terms of visuals, nothing that would be visually threatening or triggering.

Author: ChrisInVancouver (chrisinvancouver)
Author Id: 1294460037267193913
Avatar URL: assets\173bb31c158e66d28fb7004e2145c997-58F17.png
Content: As someone who worked in publishing and advertising for many years, I have some advice for people creating memes. Studies show that the spacing between letters is what determines readability. Choose fonts that have a little space (but not too much) between the letters, and leave space between lines of text. In general, italics and sizable blocks of text in all caps have worse readability. Also, try not to use too many different fonts in one image.
--------------------

Message ID: 1295577823565582439

Reply to: 1295540645779345418
Timestamp: 2024-10-15T02:43:43.81+00:00
Author: Megan C (IL) (politicspony)
Author Id: 1277109005134860453
Avatar URL: assets\6f775892e6c315cff9cbe308f1cd3f2f-141AC.png
Content: Hi Ruti!  I made the prototype yesterday in an online meme generator, then when I was ready to export it, the website alerted me that there would be a watermark unless I upgraded to a paid plan. So I took a screenshot of the preview screen, and that was the first version I posted yesterday. Later, I realized that the dimensions had come out non-standard in doing that workaround. After researching optimal dimensions for social media images (https://blog.hootsuite.com/social-media-image-sizes-guide/), I remade the whole thing from scratch using some image editing software on my computer, setting the canvas size to 1080 x 1350 at the beginning of the project.
--------------------

Memes found in the wild or self-made. Feel free to make some stellar memes for our volunteer work that others can share on socials. While we welcome a wide variety of humor, we do want to keep memes respectful of all people and groups, especially marginalized and oppressed groups.

Content: Ideas for anyone who can / wants to collaborate to turn them into social media content (which I’m not good at :)) . Meant to displace undecided voters’ perception of Trump better than Harris on these issues that are important to Americans. 

Perhaps with the “receipts” as the photo? Each is in a different format but “best one” could be used for all of them. 

[On GDP]
[top text] Sure, the economy grew under Trump.
[bottom text] But it grew by more under Biden-Harris.

[Energy]
[top text] Yes, “energy independence” is important.
[bottom text] Did you know that under Biden-Harris, we’re the most energy independent we’ve ever been?

[Stock Market]
[top text] A President who’s good for the stock market and your 401k?
[bottom text] The stock market’s never been higher than under Biden-Harris. 

[Jobs]
[top text] An administration that creates jobs for Americans?
[bottom text] Under Biden-Harris, there are now 6 million more jobs than pre-pandemic. 

[top text] Hate those extra fees when buying concert tickets?
[bottom text] Tim Walz banned them in Minnesota, & Biden-Harris proposed it in Washington. 

Can’t Congress agree on anything?
Under Biden-Harris, they started to:
- Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act
-CHIPS and Science Act - make critical chips in USA, not China
-Bipartisan Safer Communities Act - common sense gun control
-PACT Act - Vets benefits
-Electoral Count Reform Act - election security
-Border Bill - drafted by bipartisan committee, supported by Border Patrol, Pres, VP (not passed)
-or-

-Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act
